### Implement Bubble Tea update method to handle messages in Go

Source: https://github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea/blob/main/tutorials/commands/README.md

This Go code defines the `Update` method for the Bubble Tea model. It handles `statusMsg` and `errMsg` by updating the model's state and returning `tea.Quit` to exit the application. It also includes a case for `tea.KeyPressMsg` to handle Ctrl+C for quitting.

```go
func (m model) Update(msg tea.Msg) (tea.Model, tea.Cmd) {
    switch msg := msg.(type) {

    case statusMsg:
        // The server returned a status message. Save it to our model. Also
        // tell the Bubble Tea runtime we want to exit because we have nothing
        // else to do. We'll still be able to render a final view with our
        // status message.
        m.status = int(msg)
        return m, tea.Quit

    case errMsg:
        // There was an error. Note it in the model. And tell the runtime
        // we're done and want to quit.
        m.err = msg
        return m, tea.Quit

    case tea.KeyPressMsg:
        // Ctrl+c exits. Even with short running programs it's good to have
        // a quit key, just in case your logic is off. Users will be very
        // annoyed if they can't exit.
		if msg.Mod == tea.ModCtrl && msg.Code == 'c' {
			return m, tea.Quit
		}
    }

    // If we happen to get any other messages, don't do anything.
    return m, nil
}

```

--------------------------------

### Implement Update Method for Bubble Tea Model (Go)

Source: https://github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea/blob/main/tutorials/basics/README.md

Implements the 'Update' method for the Bubble Tea model. This function handles incoming messages (like key presses) and updates the model's state accordingly. It manages cursor movement, item selection, and program exit commands.

```go
func (m model) Update(msg tea.Msg) (tea.Model, tea.Cmd) {
    switch msg := msg.(type) {

    // Is it a key press?
    case tea.KeyPressMsg:

        // Cool, what was the actual key pressed?
        switch msg.String() {

        // These keys should exit the program.
        case "ctrl+c", "q":
            return m, tea.Quit

        // The "up" and "k" keys move the cursor up
        case "up", "k":
            if m.cursor > 0 {
                m.cursor--
            }

        // The "down" and "j" keys move the cursor down
        case "down", "j":
            if m.cursor < len(m.choices)-1 {
                m.cursor++
            }

        // The enter key and the space bar toggle the selected state for the
        // item that the cursor is pointing at.
        case "enter", "space":
            _, ok := m.selected[m.cursor]
            if ok {
                delete(m.selected, m.cursor)
            } else {
                m.selected[m.cursor] = struct{}{}
            }
        }
    }

    // Return the updated model to the Bubble Tea runtime for processing.
    // Note that we're not returning a command.
    return m, nil
}
```

--------------------------------

### Run a Bubble Tea Program

Source: https://github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea/blob/main/README.md

Initializes and runs a Bubble Tea program with the provided initial model. Handles potential errors during program execution.

```go
func main() {
    p := tea.NewProgram(initialModel())
    if _, err := p.Run(); err != nil {
        fmt.Printf("Alas, there's been an error: %v", err)
        os.Exit(1)
    }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Implement Bubble Tea initialization method returning a command in Go

Source: https://github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea/blob/main/tutorials/commands/README.md

This Go code implements the `Init` method for the Bubble Tea model. It returns the `checkServer` command, indicating that the HTTP request should be initiated when the application starts. The Bubble Tea runtime will execute this command.

```go
func (m model) Init() tea.Cmd {
    return checkServer
}

```

### Bubble Tea Basics > The Update Method

Source: https://github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea/blob/main/tutorials/basics/README.md

The **Update** method is the heart of a Bubble Tea application's interactivity. It receives messages (`tea.Msg`), which represent events like key presses, timer ticks, or network responses. Using a type switch, the `Update` function determines the type of message and modifies the application's model accordingly. It can also return a `tea.Cmd` to trigger further actions or I/O. For instance, handling key presses involves checking which key was pressed and updating the model's state, such as moving a cursor or toggling a selection. Special commands like `tea.Quit` can be returned to gracefully exit the application.

